Germany's new battleship, postponed again
The German Navy's new frigate was supposed to have been completed in 2014 to replace the Cold War-era warships, but will not be completed until at least next year due to faulty systems and rising costs, according to local media.
The completion of the "Rheinland-Pfalz", the lead ship of the new Baden-Württemberg-class frigates, has been postponed until the first half of 2019, according to the newspaper Die Zeit, citing a military spokesman.
