American star Phil Mickelson, who fought for most of the tournament, threw the opening shot into the water at the par 3 16th hole, which ceded the victory to Francesco Molinari.
Italian golfer Molinari shone in all of his series and became one of only four players to have achieved a 5-0-0 record since the current format of the tournament began in 1979.
American Jordan Spieth was dismissed with a 5&4 by the least qualified player of the European team Thorbjorn Olesen, from Denmark.
The world's most skilled player, Dustin Johnson, lost 2-1 to Ian Poulter of England, who might have played his last Ryder Cup.
Eight-time Ryder Cup winner Sergio Garcia became the tournament's all-time leading scorer with 25.5 career points.
"I don't usually cry, but today I can't help it.
It's been a very tough year.
Thank you, Thomas, for choosing me and believing in me.
I'm so happy, so happy to have the cup back.
The team is the most important thing... and I'm glad I was able to help", said an excited Garcia after the European victory.
He passes the baton to his compatriot John Ram, who defeated American golf legend Tiger Woods 2&1 in an individual competition on Sunday.
"I'm incredibly proud to have won Tiger Woods, I grew up following him", said Rahm, 23.
Woods lost all four matches he had in France and now has a career Ryder Cup record of 13-21-3.
A strange statistic for one of the greatest players to ever play the game, with 14 major titles won and only behind Jack Nicklaus.
The U.S. team struggled all weekend to find the streets, with the exception of Patrick Reed, Justin Thomas and Tony Finau, who played top-class golf throughout the tournament.
U.S. captain Jim Furyk spoke after his team's frustrating performance: "I'm proud of these players, they've fought.
There was a moment this morning when we pressed the European selection.
We fought.
I take my hat off to Thomas.
He's a great captain.
Your 12 players have played very well.
We're gonna regroup, work with the PGA of America and our Ryder Cup committee, and we're gonna make progress.
I love these 12 players and I'm proud to have been their captain.
You've got to take off your hat.
We have been defeated".
Red tide update: concentrations are decreasing in Pinellas, Manatee and Sarasota
The latest report from the Florida Fish and Wildlife Commission shows a general reduction in red tide concentrations in certain parts of the Tampa Bay area.
According to the FWC, more dispersed proliferation conditions are being reported in the Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Charlotte, and Collier areas, suggesting a lower concentration.
The red tide's proliferation extends along approximately 200 km of coastline, from northern Pinellas to southern Lee counties.
Spots can be found 10 miles off the coast of Hillsborough County, but in fewer places, compared to last week's situation.
Red tide has also been observed in Pasco County.
Medium concentrations have been reported onshore or offshore in Pinellas County over the past week, low to high concentrations offshore in Hillsborough County, deep or high concentrations in Manatee County, medium to deep concentrations in Charlotte County, deep to high concentrations onshore or offshore in Lee County, and low concentrations in Collier County.
Respiratory irritation is continuing to be reported in Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Lee and Collier counties.
There have been no reports of respiratory irritation throughout the past week in northeast Florida.
